    ("""Chelsea were elected to the Football League Second Division immediately upon formation and won promotion to the First Division in only their second season, in 1907. The club quickly became one of the most popular in London. By the late 1910s, Chelsea had become the first club in Britain to average over 40,000 spectators per match, reflecting enormous support from the local community. The club signed Nils Middelboe, a Danish international, in 1913, making him the first non-British player in the Football League. In 1915, Chelsea reached the FA Cup Final — known as the Khaki Cup Final due to wartime conditions — but lost 3–0 to Sheffield United at Old Trafford. During this period the club was nicknamed 'The Pensioners', a reference to the Chelsea Pensioners, retired soldiers who lived at the Royal Hospital Chelsea nearby.""", None),

